def bin_num_var(col, n_bin=255):
    
    non_nan_idx = ~col.isnull()
    col_non_nan = col[non_nan_idx]
    n_sample = col_non_nan.shape[0]
    col_non_nan_sort = col_non_nan.sort_values()
    s_order = pd.Series(list(range(n_sample)))
    bin_size = int(n_sample / n_bin)
    if bin_size != (n_sample / n_bin):
        bin_size += 1
    col_non_nan_group = s_order.apply(lambda x: int(x / bin_size) + 1)
    col_non_nan_group.index = col_non_nan_sort.index
    col_non_nan_group = col_non_nan_group[col_non_nan.index]
    
    col_group = col * np.nan
    col_group[non_nan_idx] = col_non_nan_group
    return col_group

def visual_analysis_num(x_col, y_col, col_name_disp):
    """view relationship to error for numerical variables, summarize for NaN separately"""
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15, 6))
    ax1 = fig.add_subplot(121)
    ax2 = fig.add_subplot(122)
    group_median = y_col.groupby(x_col).median()
    group_median = group_median.sort_index()
    sns.countplot(x_col, order=list(group_median.index), ax=ax1).set_title('density')
    ax1.set_xticks([])
    sns.regplot(group_median.index.values, group_median.values, fit_reg=False, ax=ax2).set_title('group pred median')
    ax2.set_xticks([])
    fig.suptitle('exploration for %s' % col_name_disp)
    fig.show()


def visual_analysis_cat(x_col, y_col, col_name_disp, rm_xticks=False, sort_by_index=False):
    """view relationship to error for categorical variables"""
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15, 6))
    ax1 = fig.add_subplot(121)
    ax2 = fig.add_subplot(122)
    group_median = y_col.groupby(x_col).median()
    if sort_by_index:
        group_median = group_median.sort_index()
    else:
        group_median = group_median.sort_values()
    sns.countplot(x_col, order=list(group_median.index), ax=ax1).set_title('density')
    if rm_xticks:
        ax1.set_xticks([])
    range_ticks = np.array(range(group_median.shape[0]))
    sns.regplot(range_ticks, group_median.values, fit_reg=False, ax=ax2).set_title('group pred median')
    xticks = [] if rm_xticks else range_ticks
    ax2.set_xticks(xticks)
    if not rm_xticks:
        ax2.set_xticklabels(list(group_median.index))
    fig.suptitle('exploration for %s' % col_name_disp)
    fig.show()
In [34]:
for col in z.feature_info.index:
    if z.feature_info.loc[col, 'type'] == 'cat' or col[:3] == 'num':
        if z.feature_info.loc[col, 'class'] == 3:
            visual_analysis_cat(x_raw[col], pred_error1, col, True)
        else:
            visual_analysis_cat(x_raw[col], pred_error1, col)
    elif z.feature_info.loc[col, 'type'] == 'num':
        if col == 'year_assess':
            visual_analysis_cat(x_raw[col], pred_error1, col)
        else:
            col_group = bin_num_var(x_raw[col])
            visual_analysis_num(col_group, pred_error1, col)
